text: I eaten for so many years wonton noodle. I have to say was treated a few half slices nice char siew. Noodle not sprungy type. Normal critic. See photo for comment.
Roast duck is black and hard, probably that's why the stall name has the word charcoal. Hor fun portion is small. Otherwise, taste is ok

Don’t bother coming here. Bunch of cheat and beggars. Use your cdc voucher at risk as they will over charge you. $4.30 but ask to redeem for $5 because they don’t accept part cash part vouchers. And when they charge $5 - no change given. And when you complain, grab food out from hand and throw away. They knew their scam were up when he gave back the cash.

Take them off the cdc plan as they don’t deserve it.
Just tried their dang gui duck and char siew. Duck was tender with herbal notes. Dang gui sauce was superb. Char siew was nicely charred and fatty. Prices reasonable too!
Char siew is good very tender. The duck skin is less fat and roast perfectly.
